ATHENS , July 20 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Senior foreign ministry officials of Greece and Turkey would meet in Ankara next Monday to discuss bilateral cooperation in the fields of culture and economy .
Announcing this at a press briefing , Greek government spokesman Dimitris Reppas said Tuesday that the next round of talks between senior diplomats of the two countries , which will take place in Athens , would focus on issues such as combating crime , illegal immigrants terrorism and related issues .
The Greek delegation to Ankara would be headed by two foreign ministry ambassadors .
The Ankara talks come following the New York meeting between Greek Foreign Minister George Papandreou and his Turkish counterpart , Ismail Cem , late June .
Greece and Turkey , both NATO members have been at odds over decades for their disputes in the territorial waters , air space limits and the delimitation of the continental shelf in the Aegean Sea and the Cyprus problem .
In recent months , the two neighboring countries have made efforts to improve their strained relations .
